   "source": [
    "# Deployment Strategies: Safe Rollout of New Models\n\n## Learning Objectives\n- Compare deployment strategies (canary, blue-green, rolling, shadow)\n- Understand risk management in deployment\n- Design monitoring for detection and rollback\n- Handle deployment failures gracefully\n\n## Interview Questions This Covers\n- \"How do you deploy new model without affecting users?\"\n- \"Canary takes 3 days. How do you speed up?\"\n- \"Design deployment for 100 models across company\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Basic: Deployment Strategy Comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n\nstrategies = pd.DataFrame({\n    'Strategy': ['Canary', 'Blue-Green', 'Rolling', 'Shadow'],\n    'Risk': ['Low (5%)', 'None (instant switch)', 'Medium (gradual)', 'None (unused)'],\n    'Rollback Time': ['Instant', 'Instant', '15-30min', 'N/A'],\n    'Speed': ['3 days', 'Instant', '1 day', '1 week validation'],\n    'Cost': ['1x', '2x (dual infra)', '1x', '1x'],\n    'When to Use': ['Most models', 'Critical+cash', 'Performance ok', 'Pre-canary test']\n})\n\nprint(\"DEPLOYMENT STRATEGY COMPARISON\")\nprint()\nprint(strategies.to_string(index=False))\nprint()\n\nprint(\"CANARY DEPLOYMENT (Most Common)\")\nprint(\"  Day 1: 5% traffic (8h monitoring)\")\nprint(\"  Day 2: 25% traffic (8h monitoring)\")\nprint(\"  Day 3: 50% traffic (8h monitoring)\")\nprint(\"  Day 3+: 100% traffic\")\nprint(\"  Any issues: instant rollback\")\nprint()\n\nprint(\"BLUE-GREEN DEPLOYMENT (Critical Systems)\")\nprint(\"  Blue: current model (100% traffic)\")\nprint(\"  Green: new model (deployed, tested)\")\nprint(\"  Switch: router instantly routes 100% → Green\")\nprint(\"  If issue: instant switch back to Blue\")\nprint(\"  Cost: need 2x infrastructure (expensive)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Advanced: Canary Deployment with Auto-Rollback"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "canary_deployment = '''\nCanary Deployment Workflow:\n\n1. PREPARE NEW MODEL\n   - Version: myregistry.com/model:v1.1.0\n   - Tested and ready\n   - Previous version: myregistry.com/model:v1.0.0 (available for rollback)\n\n2. DEPLOY CANARY (5% TRAFFIC)\n   kubectl set image deployment/model model=myregistry.com/model:v1.1.0\n   kubectl set resources deployment/model --replicas=1  # 1 canary pod\n   Result: 1 pod running v1.1.0, 19 pods running v1.0.0\n   Traffic split: Kubernetes router sends 5% → v1.1.0, 95% → v1.0.0\n\n3. MONITORING (24 HOURS)\n   Metrics checked every minute:\n   - Latency: p99 should match v1.0.0\n   - Error rate: should be <1%\n   - Accuracy: compared via A/B test on subset\n   - Business metrics: engagement, revenue\n\n4. AUTO-ROLLBACK (IF METRICS DEGRADE)\n   If any metric exceeds threshold:\n     kubectl set image deployment/model model=myregistry.com/model:v1.0.0\n   Result: v1.1.0 pod killed, traffic routed back to v1.0.0\n   Time to rollback: <30 seconds\n\n5. GRADUAL EXPANSION (IF METRICS GOOD)\n   24h after canary, if all metrics passed:\n     kubectl set resources deployment/model --replicas=5  # 5 pods v1.1.0\n   New traffic split: 25% → v1.1.0, 75% → v1.0.0\n   \n   After 24h more:\n     kubectl set resources deployment/model --replicas=10  # 10 pods\n   Traffic split: 50% → v1.1.0, 50% → v1.0.0\n   \n   After 24h more:\n     kubectl set image deployment/model model=myregistry.com/model:v1.1.0 (all)\n   Traffic split: 100% → v1.1.0\n\nTOTAL TIME: 3 days from canary to full deployment\n'''\n\nprint(\"CANARY DEPLOYMENT WITH AUTO-ROLLBACK\")\nprint()\nprint(canary_deployment)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Real-World Examples: Netflix, Stripe, Uber"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execute_count": null,
   "id": "cell-4",\n    "metadata": {},\n    "outputs": [],\n    "source": [\n      "examples = '''\nNETFLIX: All Models Use Canary\n- Strategy: 5% users for 24h\n- Metrics: watch_hours, engagement, latency\n- Frequency: 50+ new models deployed per day\n- Automation: canary expansion happens automatically if metrics pass\n- Result: safe, consistent deployment process\n\nSTRIPE: Blue-Green for Fraud (Critical)\n- Strategy: instant traffic switch (fraud affects revenue directly)\n- Preparation: 1-week shadow test before deployment\n- Deployment: green model warmed up, then instant switch\n- Monitoring: 24h continuous, auto-rollback if detection < 95%\n- Fallback: if any issues, instant blue/green switch back\n\nUBER: Variable Speed Based on Risk\n- Low-risk (optimization): 10% canary, 6h windows (fast: 24h total)\n- Medium-risk (model change): 5% canary, 24h windows (standard: 3 days)\n- High-risk (infrastructure): 1% canary, 48h windows, on-call engineer (careful: 5+ days)\n- Result: balance speed for low-risk, safety for high-risk\n'''\n\n      print(examples)\n    ]\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-1",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## Interview Case Study: Designing Deployment for 100 Models\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "code",\n   "execution_count": null,\n   "id": "cell-6",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "outputs": [],\n   "source": [\n    "case_study = '''\nSCENARIO: ML Ops platform with 100 models in production\n- Each model deployed independently\n- Need: safe, fast, standardized deployment\n\nDESIGN DEPLOYMENT STRATEGY:\n\n1. BASELINE STRATEGY: Canary for All\n   - Default: 5% traffic, 24h windows\n   - Expansion: 5% → 25% → 50% → 100% (3 days total)\n   - Monitoring: latency, error rate, business metrics\n   - Auto-rollback if any metric degrades >2%\n\n2. VARIATIONS BY RISK LEVEL\n   Low-risk (bug fix, optimization):\n   - 10% canary, 6h windows\n   - Faster: 1 day to full deployment\n   - Rationale: lower risk, test fast\n   \n   Medium-risk (model retrain, feature change):\n   - 5% canary, 24h windows (standard)\n   \n   High-risk (major architecture change):\n   - 1% canary, 48h windows\n   - Requires on-call engineer monitoring\n   - 1-week shadow test before canary\n   - Slower, but safer for critical models\n   \n   Critical (fraud, payment):\n   - Blue-green deployment\n   - 2x infrastructure cost\n   - Instant switch + instant rollback\n   - No canary phase (binary: blue or green)\n\n3. INFRASTRUCTURE FOR SCALE\n   - Kubernetes for orchestration\n   - Flagger or Istio for traffic splitting\n   - Automated monitoring and alert system\n   - Central dashboard showing all 100 models\n   - Auto-rollback configured per model\n\n4. APPROVAL WORKFLOW\n   - Low-risk: auto-approve, canary immediately\n   - Medium-risk: 1 engineer approval, 30min review\n   - High-risk: 2 engineer approvals, thorough review\n   - Critical: manual approval + on-call engineer\n\n5. MONITORING ACROSS 100 MODELS\n   - Unified metrics dashboard\n   - Latency alerts: per-model p99 > SLO\n   - Accuracy alerts: per-model accuracy drop > 2%\n   - Fairness alerts: per-group performance gap > 3%\n   - Business metric alerts: revenue/engagement drops\n   - Auto-rollback: if critical threshold exceeded\n\nRESULT: Standardized, safe deployment for 100 models\n- Low-risk: 1 day deployment\n- Medium-risk: 3 day deployment\n- High-risk: 5+ day deployment\n- All with auto-rollback and continuous monitoring\n'''\n\n      print(case_study)\n    ]\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   "cell_type": "markdown",\n   "id": "cell-1",\n   "metadata": {},\n   "source": [\n    "## Key Takeaways\\n\\n**Deployment strategy = risk management.** Start small (5%), monitor continuously, expand gradually.\\n\\n**Canary is standard:** Limits blast radius, enables fast feedback, safe rollback.\\n\\n**Blue-green for critical:** Instant switch useful only when infrastructure cost acceptable.\\n\\n**Common pattern:** 5% → 25% → 50% → 100% over 3 days, with auto-rollback if metrics degrade.\"\n   ]\n  }\n ],\n \"metadata\": {\n  \"kernelspec\": {\n   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n   \"language\": \"python\",\n   \"name\": \"python3\"\n  },\n  \"language_info\": {\n   \"name\": \"python\",\n   \"version\": \"3.9.0\"\n  }\n },\n \"nbformat\": 4,\n \"nbformat_minor\": 5\n}\nEOF
